{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, a portion of which has already been restituted. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionately high for this amount and lack of criminal history. A sentence of 6 months acknowledges the severity of the fiduciary breach while allowing for rehabilitation, considering the defendant's cooperative efforts in repayment.",
  "verdict": 6
}
